20a%20veterinarian.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63b5f36f1c748000180689c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESeventyFour%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20the%20most%20effective%20dewormer%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20different%20parasite%20preventives%20cover%20many%20different%20parasites%2C%20no%20one%20product%20covers%20every%20single%20internal%20and%20external%20parasite%20that%20could%20affect%20your%20dog.%20Talk%20to%20your%20veterinarian%20to%20help%20you%20decide%20which%20product%20will%20be%20best%20for%20your%20dog.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20most%20important%20part%20of%20having%20a%20relationship%20with%20a%20veterinarian%20in%20your%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Smits%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20trained%20to%20know%20what%20parasite%20problems%20we%20have%20in%20our%20area%20are%2C%20what%20lifestyle%20risks%20are%20important%20to%20consider%2C%20and%20overall%2C%20what%20is%20best%20for%20an%20individual%20pet%20and%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3ECan%20I%20deworm%20my%20dog%20myself%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20some%20dewormers%20are%20available%20without%20a%20prescription%2C%20do%20not%20skip%20the%20vet%20visit%20since%20different%20drugs%20treat%20different%20worms.%20Your%20vet%20will%20perform%20a%20physical%20exam%20and%20a%20fecal%20test%20to%20determine%20what%20type%20of%20worms%20they%20have.%20%26quot%3BNot%20all%20intestinal%20parasites%20are%20created%20equal%20and%20there%20is%20not%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20deworming%20medications%2C%26quot%3B%20Lay%20said.%20Although%20a%20broad-spectrum%20dewormer%20kills%20several%20different%20types%20of%20worms%2C%20certain%20single-celled%20microscopic%20parasites%20(protozoa)%2C%20including%20coccidia%20and%20Giardia%2C%20are%20not%20true%20worms.%20They%20require%20different%20prescription%20medications%20to%20treat%20them.%20Your%20dog%20also%20might%20need%20follow-up%20deworming%20and%20another%20fecal%20exam%20to%20ensure%20no%20parasites%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20natural%20dewormers%20work%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENatural%20dewormers%20aren't%20necessarily%20a%20better%20option%2C%20so%20you%20should%20check%20with%20your%20veterinarian%20before%20giving%20one%20to%20your%20dog.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20'natural'%20deworming%20products%20may%20have%20some%20effect%20on%20intestinal%20parasites%2C%20I've%20consulted%20with%20numerous%20clients%20over%20the%20years%20who%20have%20tried%20them%20with%20repeated%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20Lay%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20conventional%2C%20veterinarian-recommended%20dewormers%20have%20gone%20through%20stringent%20drug%20trials%20and%20studies%20to%20prove%20they%20are%20effective%20and%20safe%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%20I%20give%20my%20dog%20to%20prevent%20worms%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EVeterinarians%20recommend%20keeping%20dogs%20on%20a%20broad-spectrum%20parasite%20preventive%20all%20year%2C%20not%20only%20in%20the%20spring%20and%20summer%20months.%20Different%20parasites%20are%20active%20during%20different%20months%2C%20and%20parasite%20activity%20varies.%20Parasites%20can%20also%20become%20active%20earlier%20than%20expected%2C%20including%20during%20the%20winter.%20%26quot%3BMany%20adult%20dogs%20may%20be%20asymptomatic%20carriers%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Kelley%20Lay%2C%20a%20relief%20veterinarian%20who%20practices%20in%20Nashville%2C%20Tennessee.%20%26quot%3BParasites%20are%20not%20always%20able%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20feces%20and%20so%20you%20may%20not%20even%20know%20the%20problem%20is%20there.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20infections%20that%20linger%20undetected%20for%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETypes%20of%20worms%20and%20their%20signs%20and%20symptoms%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20golden%20retriever%20sniffing%20another%20dog%2C%20featured%20in%20best%20dog%20dewormers%20in%202022%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6099a193342837001822ca24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221124%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChristiane%20Bongertz%2FEyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20dogs%20will%20contract%20intestinal%20parasites%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20lives.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20common%20worms%20seen%20in%20dogs%20are%20roundworms%2C%20tapeworms%2C%20hookworms%2C%20and%20whipworms.%20In%20adult%20dogs%2C%20parasite%20infestations%20may%20cause%20mild%20to%20moderate%20digestive%20symptoms%20like%20vomiting%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20and%20gas.%20However%2C%20heavy%20infestations%2C%20especially%20in%20young%20puppies%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20severe%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20cause%20intestinal%20problems%2C%20malnutrition%2C%20anemia%2C%20growth%20problems%20in%20puppies%2C%20and%20even%20potential%20autoimmune%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20Smits%20said.%20%26quot%3BAlso%20important%20is%20the%20zoonotic%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20potential%20spread%20to%20human%20family%20members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoundworms%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThese%20parasites%20are%20common%20in%20dogs%2C%20especially%20puppies%2C%20and%20are%203-%20to%206-inches%20long%2C%20smooth%2C%20and%20round-bodied.%20You%20might%20not%20know%20your%20dog%20has%20roundworms%2C%20particularly%20if%20they%20have%20only%20a%20few.%20In%20puppies%2C%20large%20numbers%20of%20worms%20may%20cause%20a%20pot-bellied%20appearance%2C%20vomiting%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20low%20appetite%2C%20dull%20coat%2C%20and%20restricted%20growth.%20You%20might%20also%20see%20roundworms%20in%20your%20dog's%20stool%20or%20vomit.%20Roundworms%20are%20zoonotic%2C%20which%20means%20they%20can%20be%20spread%20to%20human%20family%20members.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETapeworms%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDogs%20pick%20up%20tapeworms%20when%20they%20ingest%20an%20infected%20adult%20flea.%20As%20the%20tapeworm%20grows%2C%20segments%20break%20off%20and%20pass%20in%20your%20dog's%20stool.%20If%20you%20see%20something%20in%20your%20dog's%20feces%20that%20resembles%20grains%20of%20white%20rice%2C%20or%20you%20notice%20them%20licking%20or%20biting%20the%20area%20under%20their%20tail%2C%20they%20could%20have%20a%20tapeworm%20infestation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHookworms%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHookworms%20are%20blood-sucking%20parasites%20that%20attach%20to%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20intestines.%20These%20tiny%20worms%20are%20nearly%20invisible%20without%20the%20assistance%20of%20a%20microscope.%20Signs%20of%20hookworm%20infection%20in%20dogs%20include%20anemia%2C%20weight%20loss%2C%20bloody%20diarrhea%2C%20dull%20coat%2C%20and%20growth%20restriction.%20Hookworms%20are%20zoonotic%20so%20they%20can%20be%20spread%20to%20human%20family%20members.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhipworms%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhipworms%20are%20relatively%20large%20intestinal%20parasites%20(about%20a%20%C2%BC-inch%20long)%20that%20reside%20in%20the%20cecum%20and%20large%20intestine%2C%20where%20they%20wreak%20serious%20havoc.%20Dogs%20with%20heavy%20whipworms%20are%20likely%20to%20experience%20concerning%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20watery%2C%20bloody%20diarrhea%2C%20weight%20loss%2C%20and%20anemia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20dewormers%3Cp%3EWhile%20researching%20and%20writing%20this%20guide%2C%20I%20drew%20from%20my%20eight%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20an%20assistant%20in%20veterinary%20hospitals%20and%20two%20decades%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20writer%20and%20editor%20in%20the%20pet%20and%20veterinary%20fields.%20I%20conducted%20research%20using%20the%20quick%20product%20reference%20guide%20published%20by%20the%20independent%2C%20nonprofit%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapcv