0natural%20justice%20as%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20not%20provided%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20complaint%2C%20or%20the%20allegations%20made%20therein%2C%20the%20petitioner%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20impugned%20order%20failed%20to%20show%20any%20incorrectness%20or%20error%20in%20the%20article%20in%20question%20but%20only%20ordered%20removal%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Cits%20incorrect%20subjective%20reading%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20order%20was%20devoid%20of%20any%20reasoning%20and%20could%20not%20show%20how%20its%20claim%20that%20the%20piece%20had%20negative%20impact%20on%20communal%20harmony%2C%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%20or%20public%20order%20was%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20mentioned%20that%20the%20requirements%20of%20necessity%20and%20expediency%20under%20Section%2069A%20have%20not%20been%20established%20by%20the%20ministry%20while%20issuing%20the%20order.%20Notably%2C%20it%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20proper%20and%20effective%20opportunity%20to%20rebut%20the%20allegations%20was%20not%20provided%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20during%20a%20hearing%2C%20which%20lasted%20only%20for%2030-35%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fread-the-caravans-article-on-army-torture-the-union-government-wants-taken-down%5C%22%3EThe%20Caravan%E2%80%99s%20Article%20on%20Army%20Torture%20the%20Union%20Government%20Wants%20Taken%20Down%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWithout%20providing%20the%20materials%20relied%20upon%2C%20the%20hearing%20was%20rendered%20a%20meaningless%20empty%20formality.%20The%20impugned%20order%20has%20thus%20gravely%20violated%20the%20free%20speech%20right%20of%20the%20petitioner%20as%20it%20is%20an%20unreasonable%2C%20excessive%2C%20and%20arbitrary%20restriction%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20press.%20The%20procedure%20adopted%20by%20the%20respondent%20has%20also%20violated%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20equality%20by%20violating%20the%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20mentioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETimeline%20of%20events%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFebruary%201%2C%202024%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%20published%20a%20long%20form%20story%20titled%20%E2%80%98Screams%20from%20the%20Army%20Post%E2%80%99%C2%A0on%20the%20incidents%20of%20abduction%2C%20torture%20and%20custodial%20killings%20of%20civilians%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20officials%20of%20the%2048%20Rashtriya%20Rifles%20counter-insurgency%20force%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%20on%20December%2022%2C%202023%20in%20Poonch%20and%20Rajouri%20districts%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20A%20video%20story%20related%20to%20the%20article%20was%20also%20posted%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20YouTube.%20After%20its%20publication%2C%20social%20media%20posts%20promoting%20the%20article%20and%20video%20story%20were%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20called%20Twitter)%20and%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFebruary%209%2C%202024%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20received%20a%20notice%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20%26amp%3B%20Broadcasting%20under%20the%20IT%20Rules%20intimating%20that%20a%20complaint%20had%20been%20received%20by%20the%20ministry%20regarding%20the%20%E2%80%98Screams%20from%20the%20Army%20Post%E2%80%99%20article%20and%20social%20media%20posts%20as%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Cdetrimental%20to%20sovereignty%20%26amp%3B%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20State%2C%20and%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20lead%20to%20communal%20tensions%20leading%20to%20disturbance%20of%20public%20order%20in%20the%20U.T.%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D.%20A%20representative%20from%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20asked%20to%20be%20present%20for%20an%20online%20meeting%20with%20the%20inter-departmental%20committee%20on%20February%2012%20at%2012%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20urls%20complained%20of%20was%20posted%20on%20X%20on%20February%204%2C%202024%20and%20was%20related%20to%20the%20ethnic%20cleansing%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur%20(article%20published%20in%20August%202023%20issue)%20and%20was%20not%20related%20to%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFebruary%2011%2C%202024%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20response%2C%20the%20editorial%20manager%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20sent%20a%20letter%20denying%20the%20allegations%20against%20the%20article%20and%20social%20media%20posts.%20The%20manager%20also%20sought%20the%20complaint%20made%20against%20the%20article%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20which%20the%20proceedings%20had%20been%20initiated%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20procedure%20that%20would%20be%20followed%20by%20the%20inter-departmental%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFebruary%2012%2C%202024%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20During%20the%20meeting%2C%20the%20committee%20members%20said%20the%20urls%20in%20question%20should%20be%20pulled%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20representative%20was%20neither%20supplied%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20request%2Fcomplaint%20nor%20provided%20the%20details%20of%20the%20complainant%2C%20the%20allegations%20therein%2C%20or%20which%20specific%20portion(s)%20of%20the%20article%20which%20was%20detrimental%20to%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20disturb%20public%20order.%20The%20main%20issue%20raised%20by%20the%20committee%20was%20that%20the%20article%20lacked%20an%20official%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20Army%20on%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20representative%20pointed%20out%20to%20the%20committee%20that%20the%20Army%20had%20not%20offered%20a%20response%20to%20the%20author%20despite%20being%20requested%20for%20interviews%20and%20being%20supplied%20with%20a%20questionnaire%20and%20that%20the%20online%20version%20of%20the%20article%20would%20be%20updated%20if%20a%20response%20was%20received%20even%20after%20publication.%20Further%2C%20the%20representative%20mentioned%20that%20there%20was%20no%20official%20denial%20or%20rebuttal%20of%20any%20of%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20article%20by%20any%20government%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20same%20day%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20exercised%20its%20power%20under%20Rule%2015%20of%20The%20Information%20Technology%20(Intermediary%20Guidelines%20and%20Digital%20Media%20Ethics%20Code)%20Rules%2C%202021%20%5B%E2%80%9CIT%20Rules%E2%80%9D%5D%20and%20issued%20an%20order%20directing%20the%20magazine%20to%20take%20down%20the%20article%20from%20its%20website%2C%20and%20certain%20URLs%20of%20social%20media%20posts%20posted%20from%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fem%3Esocial%20media%20handles%20disseminating%20the%20article.%20The%20order%20underlined%20that%20the%20website%20and%20social%20media%20links%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20lead%20to%20communal%20disharmony%20and%20uprising%20against%20the%20security%20forces%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20were%20detrimental%20to%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20public%20order%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710334841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11084916%2FScreenshot-2023-10-11-at-8.48.21-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fviolated-principles-of-natural-justice-caravan-files-petition-against-govt-order-on-army-story%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20petition%2C%20The%20Caravan%20has%20underlined%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20%26amp%3B%20Broadcasting's%20order%20asking%20the%20magazine%20to%20take%20down%20its%20article%20on%20allegations%20of%20torture%20and%20murder%20against%20the%20Indian%20Army%20also%20violated%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20and%20expression%20and%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20press.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fviolated-principles-of-natural-justice-caravan-files-petition-against-govt-order-on-army-story%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Receives%20Three%20Petitions%20a%20Day%20After%20Govt%20Notifies%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20Rules%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20At%20least%20three%20petitions%20have%20been%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20notification%20of%20the%20contentious%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(CAA).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20arguments%20in%20the%20petitions%2C%20filed%20a%20day%20after%20the%20law%20was%20notified%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20just%20days%20before%20the%20general%20elections%20are%20to%20be%20announced%2C%20range%20from%20the%20Act%20being%20%E2%80%98unconstitutional%E2%80%99%20as%20it%20is%20based%20on%20religion%2C%20to%20violating%20the%20core%20clause%20of%20the%20Assam%20Accord%20of%201985.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20petition%20filed%20at%20the%20apex%20court%20on%20March%2012%2C%20the%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%20(IUML)%20and%20the%20Democratic%20Youth%20Federation%20of%20India%20(DYFI)%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.co.in%2Furl%3Fsa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D%26cad%3Drja%26uact%3D8%26ved%3D2ahUKEwie0uLjh_GEAxV-a2wGHcwVBNAQ